HEADWORD: Spermospore
<hw>Sper"mo*spore</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Spermo-</ets> + <ets>spore</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>The male germinal or seminal cell, from the
breaking up of which the spermoblasts are formed and ultimately the
spermatozoids; a spermatospore.</def> <rj><au>Balfour.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spermule</ent>⟦br⟧
